  "commit_message": "Fix order_by/then_order_by with GROUP BY rejecting valid aggregate expressions\n\nSince `v2.3.8`, calling `order_by()` or `then_order_by()` with an aggregate\nexpression on a query that has a `group_by()` clause incorrectly failed\nto compile, even though the resulting SQL is valid. The check introduced\nin `v2.3.8` validated the `SELECT` clause against the `ORDER BY` expression at\n`order_by()` call time, which blocked valid patterns like:\n\n```rust\ntable.group_by(col).order_by(max(other_col)).select(",
